            "name": "Concerns or Challenges",
            "sections": [
                {
                    "subtitle": "Student's Concerns",
                    "components": [
                        {
                            "type": "text-paragraph",
                            "text": "Many students may not have practical experience so have questions and concerns; being on placement can be significantly different to academic assignments. Frequently asked questions and concerns include:"
                        },
                        {
                            "subtitle": "Best practice for clinical learning environment",
                            "type": "video-single",
                            "space_after": false,
                            "video": {
                                "type": "youtube",
                                "src": "http://www.youtube.com/embed/kEQeX8Gv4Ic",
                                "thumb": "kEQeX8Gv4Ic.jpg"
                            }
                        }
                    ],
                    "space_after": true
                },
                {
                    "subtitle": "Requirements",
                    "space_after": true,
                    "components": [
                        {
                            "type": "text-paragraph",
                            "text": "It is useful for students to be aware of their placement requirements before starting the placement. They can find details about the requirements through reading their placement handbook and the competencies. They can also direct any questions about these requirements to their personal tutor, learning support tutor or course leader well before the placement begins"
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "subtitle": "Myths and misconceptions about disabled students on placements",
                    "components": [
                        {
                            "type": "text-paragraph",
                            "text": "Disabled people work in many capacities as health care professionals. It is important they can meet the competencies and have the support and reasonable adjustments they need. If you are not sure about a student’s ability to meet competencies you can discuss any concerns with the disability team and regulatory bodies.",
                            "space_after": true
                        },
                        {
                            "subtitle": "Supporting Students",
                            "space_after": false,
                            "type": "text-paragraph",
                            "text": "There are many ways you can support students during this difficult period. Watch the following videos for a brief look at some of the likely situations a student will find themselves in and how you can support him/her."
                        },
