        {
            "blockname": "PrePlacement Info",
            "name": "Reasonable Adjustments",
            "sections": [
                {
                    "subtitle": "Arranging placements in time",
                    "components": [
                        {
                            "type": "text-paragraph",
                            "text": "Reasonable adjustments are changes to the work environment that allow people with disability to work safely and productively. Under the Equal Opportunity Act 2010, 'disability' includes: physical, psychological or neurological disease or disorder, illness, whether temporary or permanent.",
                            "space_after": true
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "link-website",
                            "links": [
                                {
                                    "link": "https://www.humanrightscommission.vic.gov.au/the-workplace/employer-responsibilities/reasonable-adjustments-in-employment",
                                    "text": "Reasonable Adjustments in Employment",
                                    "tag": "Human Rights Commission"
                                }
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "text-paragraph",
                            "text": "A student with a disability can legally request RA when they are going on placement. They can be supported by the Disability Team and Learning Support Tutors.",
                            "space_after": true
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "text-paragraph",
                            "text": "It is recommended that students with disabilities are placed at least 4 weeks before placement commences so they can make suitable arrangements.",
                            "subtitle": "Minimum time to prepare"
                        }
                    ],
                    "space_after": true
                },
                {
                    "subtitle": "Equality, Diversity & Inclusion",
                    "components": [
                        {
                            "type": "video-single",
                            "subtitle": "",
                            "video": {
                                "type": "youtube",
                                "src": "https://www.youtube.com/embed/C-uyB5I6WnQ",
                                "thumb": "C-uyB5I6WnQ.jpg"
                            }
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "blockname": "PrePlacement Info",
            "name": "PrePlacement Visit",
            "sections": [
                {
                    "subtitle": "Students may need a pre-placement visit.",
                    "components": [
                        {
                            "type": "text-paragraph",
                            "text": "Some students may need a pre-placement visit this could be facilitated by the Learning Support Tutor in collaboration with the placement team."
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "text-paragraph",
                            "text": "It is the student’s responsibility to prepare for a pre placement visit. Learning Support Tutors and the disability team have support mechanisms in place to support students who are organising a pre placement visit and empower them to articulate their need and think about reasonable adjustments.",
                            "space_after": true
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "video-single",
                            "subtitle": "Organising a Pre-Placement Visit",
                            "space_after": false,
                            "video": {
                                "type": "youtube",
                                "src": "https://www.youtube.com/embed/cdUx3teXih8",
                                "thumb": "cdUx3teXih8.jpg"
                            }
                        }
                    ],
                    "space_after": true
                },
                {
                    "subtitle": "Thinking Point",
                    "components": [
                        {
                            "type": "text-paragraph",
                            "text": "Why are students so anxious about placements?"
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "text-paragraph",
                            "text": "Most placements are successful. If students have all the necessary resources why do some struggle?"
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "blockname": "PrePlacement Info",
            "name": "Informing relevant people",
            "sections": [
                {
                    "subtitle": "Student Disclosure",
                    "components": [
                        {
                            "type": "text-paragraph",
                            "text": "If a student discloses a disability to the placement team, signpost them to the disability team and learning Support Tutor."
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "text-paragraph",
                            "text": "The University has a legal responsibility to support students who disclose their disability. Students will have to provide verified evidence of their disability. The disability team provides support for students going through the verification process"
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "blockname": "PrePlacement Info",
            "name": "Supporting students with a disability",
            "sections": [
                {
                    "subtitle": "Supporting students with a disability",
                    "components": [
                        {
                            "type": "text-paragraph",
                            "text": "Some students may want to have a conversation with the placement team about their disability. Placements teams can corporate with the Learning Support Tutor when discussing placements issues with students with a disability."
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "text-paragraph",
                            "text": "Some placement teams have a dedicated member staff assigned to supporting students with disabilities on placement."
                        }
                    ],
                    "space_after": true
                },
                {
                    "subtitle": "Supporting Students in Placement",
                    "components": [
                        {
                            "type": "video-carousel",
                            "subtitle": "",
                            "videos": [
                                {
                                    "type": "video-single",
