                {
                    "subtitle": "Student Health & Wellbeing",
                    "components": [
                        {
                            "type": "text-paragraph",
                            "text": "As a clinical practitioner you will engage with and educate many students in their career pathway. Within your role of supporting students you may identify that a student is struggling in clinical practice primarily due to current stressful life events in their private lives. You may have concerns about how best to support the student at these times of stress, if so the following information may be of benefit to both you and the student."
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "list-text",
                            "list_elements": [
                                {
                                    "text": "The student could be encouraged to contact their academic personal tutors (APT) who can offer pastoral support and suggest services that may be of psychological benefit for their circumstances if required."
                                },
                                {
                                    "text": "You may wish to consider and explore with the student about asking a member of the academic practice teams to visit the student for added support in the practice environment."
                                },
                                {
                                    "text": "You may wish to consider and explore with the student about asking other colleagues where appropriate such as the practice educator/ facilitators to offer the student added support at this stressful time."
                                },
                                {
                                    "text": "You may wish to consider and explore with the student whether they need to seek help and guidance from their General Practitioner."
                                },
                                {
                                    "text": "Coventry University offers a range of student Health and Wellbeing Services which includes physical, emotional and spiritual support which are confidential and accessible for the student. Two of the web links cited below from Coventry University briefly explain how the student can contact services such as the counselling services, welfare and disabilities and offers access to the “How are you today” (general wellbeing checklist web page)  which may be of benefit.",
                                    "links": []
                                },
                                {
                                    "text": "Student Services at Coventry University",
                                    "links": [
                                        {
                                            "portion": "Student Services at Coventry University",
                                            "href": "http://www.coventry.ac.uk/study-at-coventry/student-support/health-and-wellbeing/"
                                        }
                                    ]
                                },
                                {
                                    "text": "\"How are you today\" (general wellbeing checklist) at Coventry University .",
                                    "links": [
                                        {
                                            "portion": "\"How are you today\" (general wellbeing checklist) at Coventry University .",
                                            "href": "http://placementconnect.coventry.ac.uk/images/category/general_information/general_wellbeing_checklist.pdf"
                                        }
                                    ]
                                }
                            ]
                        }
                    ],
                    "space_after": true
                },
